Haruki Uemura may step down after
independent investigation finds the All Japan Judo Federation
president received 400,000 yen from the 1.2 million yen per
coach annual subsidies provided by the Japan Sport Council,
Yomiuri reports, citing Uemura speaking at a press conference
yesterday.
